  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Peroxide effect is observed with the addition of $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$ but not with the addition of HI to unsymmetrical alkene because</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{I}$$ bond is stronger than $$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{Br}$$ and is not cleaved by the free radical\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{I}$$ bond is weaker than $$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{Br}$$ bond so that iodine free radicals combine to form iodine molecules\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Bond strength of $$\\mathrm{HI}$$ and $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$ are same but free radicals are formed in $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "All of the above"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Peroxide effect is observed with addition of $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$ but not with the addition of $$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{I}$$ to unsymmetrical alkene because $$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{I}$$ bond is weaker than $$\\mathrm{H}-\\mathrm{Br}$$ bond. So, unstable iodine free radicals combine to form stable iodine molecules as</p>\n<p>i.e., <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltbpamhh/b5b25c7b-766d-401d-a1f7-e2ceace300bd/6ec7af60-d977-11ee-b24f-f7bb280a97cd/file-1ltbpamhi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltbpamhh/b5b25c7b-766d-401d-a1f7-e2ceace300bd/6ec7af60-d977-11ee-b24f-f7bb280a97cd/file-1ltbpamhi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2021 Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 13 English Explanation\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2021,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2021",
    "difficulty": null
  },
